        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 11:54PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 1154 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles north of Grindstone, or 17 miles northwest of Philip, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grindstone and Grindstone Butte.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
